 valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Book Setup</span><hr size=1> OK, now days, how do you people organize spell books?? With new mods is that not even needed??<br>
<br>
I am asking because all my eq life I have put spells in order of the level I got them at. I spent about 1 hour last night in between fights organizing it by type...i.e.damage spell, summoning spells, pet spells, utility spells, buff spells...<br>
<br>
<br>
Alantrix <p><img align=center src=http://board.rslhq.com/hosted/zonaxx/jetposse.jpg width=355 hight=73></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uazixdamage.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Azix Da Mage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#333333>(8/25/02 3:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1494.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.oek.dk/~vip/image/head.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Book Setup</span><hr size=1> I had spells organized by level - I could remember what spells I needed from what level. That did take some time to find less used spells, but I thought it would be too much of a hazzle to organize.<br>
<br>
With the new UI my spell book got really @#%$ up, so now I have 2 pages for all spells for my pet, 4 pages with different summons, 2 pages with buff spells and 2 pages with attack spells. All other spells I do not use, are still @#%$ up else where in my book. <p><table width="100%" border="0"><tr width="25%"><td rowspan="2" width="25%" align="center"></td><td width="50%" align="center"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=22508" target="new">Azix LFG</a></td><td rowspan="2" width="25%" align="center"></td></tr><tr><td height="160" align="center"><a href="http://www.nexxus.dk" target="new"><img src="http://www.oek.dk/~vip/image/sig.gif" border="0"></a></td></tr></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/umadaamstier.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mada Amstier</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#333333>(8/26/02 4:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1494.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Book Setup</span><hr size=1> I used to have him all by level as I bought em.  Then one day I got bored and reorganized them.  <br>
<br>
First 2 pages are pretty much any common spell thats loaded up from the start - mage epic, coh, modrod 2, gift of xev, mala, malosini, aegis of ro, cadeau of flame, nukes, etc.<br>
<br>
The other pages are mixed but most pets are grouped.  Other odd and end spells are grouped.  Focus items are grouped.<br>
<br>
I pretty much know what page number they are on and just load em from doing that.  Not practical but it works for me....<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ulordloralon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LordLoralon</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.legion-whiterose.com/avatars/legion.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#333333>(8/26/02 6:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1494.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.legion-whiterose.com/avatars/legion.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Book Setup</span><hr size=1> Until around lv20, I also had a spellbook by level. But the day I realised that I would never (or very rarely) use that lv1 Nuke, I organized my spellbook by category.<br>
